Linux basics

1. What is Linux?
Linux is an open-source operating system based on Unix.

2. What is Kernel?
Kernel is the core part of the OS that manages hardware and system resources.

3. What is Shell?
Shell is a command-line interpreter that allows users to interact with Linux.

4. what is operating System?
Operating System (OS):--An OS is a software that acts as an interface between computer hardware components & the user.Every computer system
